1
00:00:50,079 --> 00:00:50,920
It's me.

2
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:06,840
Who's there?

3
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:07,599
Come out!

4
00:01:09,719 --> 00:01:10,319
Password.

5
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,200
Protect peace.

6
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:12,920
And health.

7
00:01:13,879 --> 00:01:15,000
What are you two doing here?

8
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:16,719
Squad Leader, we're on guard duty.

9
00:01:17,079 --> 00:01:17,640
On guard?

10
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:20,120
What kind of guard duty is this?

11
00:01:20,359 --> 00:01:21,519
We're guarding...

12
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:22,719
the armory next door.

13
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,560
The armory's over there,

14
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,280
and behind it...

15
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:26,239
is the kitchen.

16
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,359
The kitchen's been kinda...

17
00:01:27,799 --> 00:01:28,439
Kinda what?

18
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:31,719
This whole haunting business

19
00:01:31,719 --> 00:01:32,959
really has everyone on edge.

20
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:35,640
I can't sleep at night anyway.

21
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:36,439
Tell you what,

22
00:01:36,959 --> 00:01:37,799
you two go back and get some sleep.

23
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:38,280
I'll take over for a while.

24
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:38,640
Okay.

25
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,359
Thank you, Squad Leader.

26
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,680
What on earth are you up to?

27
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,519
Catching ghosts.

28
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,799
Didn't you say there were no ghosts?

29
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:05,640
Of course there are.

30
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:06,879
Don't believe me? Watch.

31
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,639
A mirror shining bright,

32
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,000
yin-yang water grants it light.

33
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,319
All evil spirits and demons foul,

34
00:02:14,319 --> 00:02:15,639
flee to the four winds now.

35
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:17,000
Bring great fortune to my home,

36
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,199
hasten as the law commands!

37
00:02:20,439 --> 00:02:21,240
This is a demon-revealing mirror.

38
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,319
Take a look.

39
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:24,800
Hold this.

40
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,159
There's no ghost here.

41
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:35,639
Look!

42
00:02:37,599 --> 00:02:38,319
Coward.

43
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:40,280
Me?

44
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:42,319
Follow me.

45
00:02:49,199 --> 00:02:50,000
What now?

46
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:51,840
Dude,

47
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,000
isn't it obvious enough?

48
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,360
The Brigade Commander said,

49
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:55,919
without orders,

50
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,159
no one's allowed in this room.

51
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:57,919
Exactly.

52
00:02:58,439 --> 00:02:59,599
That's why I'm sneaking in.

53
00:03:00,759 --> 00:03:01,879
That's how you see it?

54
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:06,919
Unbelievable.

55
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,280
My master knows sorcery,

56
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,599
I just know how to slack off.

57
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:23,719
Don't!

58
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:25,479
Follow me.

59
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:46,439
Get in.

60
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:47,479
What for?

61
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,159
Just get in!

62
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:48,560
Hurry up.

63
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,840
What's this all about?

64
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,840
If the Company Commander catches us,

65
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:00,639
we're done for.

66
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:01,520
He'll shoot us.

67
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:03,919
After tonight,

68
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,319
who knows who'll be Company Commander.

69
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,000
Company Commander.

70
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:21,639
Company Commander.

71
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:22,800
Give me a hand!

72
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,199
This hole's too small.

73
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,519
I'm stuck.

74
00:04:26,839 --> 00:04:28,680
I told you to eat less,

75
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,480
eat less,

76
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,720
but you never listened.

77
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,079
The Brigade Commander will be back soon.

78
00:04:47,519 --> 00:04:48,399
What we've been doing

79
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:50,160
won't stay hidden much longer.

80
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,600
Tonight,

81
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,319
if we can get this shipment

82
00:04:55,319 --> 00:04:56,199
up the mountain...

83
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,160
Oh, right.

84
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:05,240
The Chief of Clear Wind Stronghold

85
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,040
gave me his word.

86
00:05:06,879 --> 00:05:07,759
As long as we get

87
00:05:07,759 --> 00:05:08,600
this batch of weapons

88
00:05:08,759 --> 00:05:09,560
up the mountain,

89
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,680
I'll be the Second-in-command.

90
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:14,759
Company Commander,

91
00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:15,480
what about me?

92
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,600
You're not gonna make me cook again, are you?

93
00:05:18,759 --> 00:05:20,040
Look at how small you dream.

94
00:05:20,839 --> 00:05:21,639
When the time comes,

95
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:23,959
I'll make you Third-in-command.

96
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,800
That'd be great!

97
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,079
Third-in-command!

98
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:29,279
Company Commander!

99
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:30,879
Thank you, Company Commander!

100
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:31,600
Thank you!

101
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:32,759
Enough.

102
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:33,600
Stop dawdling.

103
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:34,839
Get to work.

104
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:35,639
Right.

105
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,839
Third-in-command!

106
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,480
Stop.

107
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:46,959
Are you stupid?

108
00:05:47,959 --> 00:05:48,399
What?

109
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,800
Go grab the big stuff.

110
00:05:50,959 --> 00:05:52,160
This junk isn't worth a damn.

111
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:53,519
Go!

112
00:05:54,879 --> 00:05:55,399
Got it, got it.

113
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,079
Idiot.

114
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,360
This stuff is worthless.

115
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:18,959
What do we do now?

116
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,000
One each, you and me.

117
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:22,600
Can we pull it off?

118
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,120
Don't worry.

119
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:25,720
My master taught me martial arts.

120
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:05,199
You...

121
00:07:06,079 --> 00:07:07,279
Isn't being Company Commander good enough?

122
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,160
Why become a bandit?

123
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:10,399
Brother,

124
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,720
let me tell you.

125
00:07:12,519 --> 00:07:14,360
When our Brigade Commander was just a Company Commander,

126
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,279
I was already with him,

127
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:17,439
risking life and limb.

128
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,439
I even saved his life twice.

129
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:20,879
And what happened?

130
00:07:21,639 --> 00:07:22,519
He did just fine.

131
00:07:22,759 --> 00:07:24,240
He became Brigade Commander himself,

132
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,920
and all he gave me

133
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,560
was a measly Company Commander post.

134
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:32,160
That's still better than being a bandit.

135
00:07:37,439 --> 00:07:39,079
Who's beating up my disciple?

136
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,639
Who the hell are you?

137
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,000
Your funeral lantern bearer is here.

138
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:56,560
Funeral lantern for me?

139
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:02,120
You old corpse-in-waiting!

140
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,680
Give me your life!

141
00:08:24,839 --> 00:08:25,439
Dongsheng!

142
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:26,879
Dong...

143
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,200
Dongsheng!

144
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:36,759
Dongsheng!

145
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:37,919
Dongsheng!

146
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:41,480
Last night,

147
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,440
what on earth happened?

148
00:08:56,879 --> 00:08:57,559
Did you do this?

149
00:08:57,799 --> 00:08:58,360
No.

150
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,440
It was Master.

151
00:09:18,879 --> 00:09:19,200
That

152
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:22,000
backstabbing piece of trash!

153
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,679
You think it's easy building up my stash?

154
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:29,039
And he tried to hand it to bandits!

155
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,279
Brigade Commander, please calm down.

156
00:09:31,519 --> 00:09:32,039
Calm down.

157
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,320
I never imagined

158
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,799
that in my jurisdiction at Yin-Yang Crossing,

159
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,279
something like this could happen.

160
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:37,960
I bear responsibility.

161
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:41,120
The hell you do.

162
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,720
I'm the one who failed to discipline my men.

163
00:09:46,799 --> 00:09:48,000
What's it got to do with you?

164
00:09:48,799 --> 00:09:49,440
Right, right, right.

165
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:52,600
However,

166
00:09:53,279 --> 00:09:55,159
within your jurisdiction,

167
00:09:55,919 --> 00:09:57,320
there are actually bandits.

168
00:09:58,399 --> 00:09:58,840
This...

169
00:09:59,519 --> 00:10:00,840
This is your responsibility.

170
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:01,840
Exactly.

171
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:02,759
Isn't that why I've been waiting

172
00:10:02,759 --> 00:10:03,639
for the Brigade Commander to return,

173
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,039
to bring me justice?

174
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:05,440
Right.

175
00:10:05,639 --> 00:10:06,240
My brother-in-law,

176
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,039
the Mayor,

177
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,720
has been counting every star and moon,

178
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:11,159
hoping you'd return soon.

179
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:13,519
Brigade Commander, you've just returned.

180
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,440
I've prepared some humble drinks

181
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,080
to welcome you back, how about it?

182
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:19,960
You know what,

183
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,480
I am a bit hungry.

184
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,360
Then let's

185
00:10:24,879 --> 00:10:25,600
grab a quick bite.

186
00:10:25,799 --> 00:10:26,320
Grab a quick bite.

187
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:27,679
After you.

188
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,080
After you.

189
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:31,320
Shuisheng,

190
00:10:32,679 --> 00:10:33,679
come along with him.

191
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,080
Let me treat the two of you.

192
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,000
Yes, sir.

193
00:10:36,159 --> 00:10:36,559
Yes, sir.

194
00:10:37,919 --> 00:10:38,440
Come, come, come.

195
00:10:38,519 --> 00:10:38,879
Please.

196
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:39,399
Brigade Commander,

197
00:10:39,519 --> 00:10:40,240
you've worked hard.

198
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:40,919
Here.

199
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,080
This cup,

200
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:42,919
I toast to you.

201
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:43,960
I'll drink first as a sign of respect.

202
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,000
Brigade Commander,

203
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,440
I haven't used these chopsticks.

204
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:54,600
Let me get you a piece of tofu.

205
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,159
Have a taste.

206
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,399
Why are you two just standing there

207
00:11:07,399 --> 00:11:07,960
like idiots?

208
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:09,080
Come over.

209
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:09,960
Sit down and eat.

210
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:10,919
Thank you, Brigade Commander.

211
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,519
Thank you, Brigade Commander.

212
00:11:11,559 --> 00:11:12,519
Come on, come on.

213
00:11:13,279 --> 00:11:14,039
Help yourselves.

214
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:16,759
Brigade Commander.

215
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:18,039
May I propose a toast to you?

216
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,399
Then I must join you.

217
00:11:21,279 --> 00:11:22,120
It's just a simple meal.

218
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,679
Is there something not to your taste?

219
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:27,840
Only caring about your own stomach, huh?

220
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:28,440
From now on,

221
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,279
look after them.

222
00:11:29,799 --> 00:11:30,480
Just eat this.

223
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,440
What do you want to eat?

224
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:32,559
I want meatballs.

225
00:11:32,879 --> 00:11:33,600
A hearty dish, huh?

226
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:34,879
It's in the back.

227
00:11:36,639 --> 00:11:37,559
Just a little.

228
00:11:44,919 --> 00:11:45,519
These two.

229
00:11:47,519 --> 00:11:48,120
Shuisheng.

230
00:11:48,639 --> 00:11:49,759
Where did this young fellow

231
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:50,519
come from?

232
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,200
I haven't seen him before.

233
00:11:54,759 --> 00:11:55,279
Reporting, Brigade Commander.

234
00:11:55,879 --> 00:11:57,200
He's a new recruit from the draft.

235
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,080
His name is Dongsheng.

236
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,200
His master...

237
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,279
He's a good man.

238
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,039
You two,

239
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:05,960
this time you've

240
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,320
performed a great service.

241
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:08,840
Shuisheng,

242
00:12:09,679 --> 00:12:10,480
from now on,

243
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:11,639
you

244
00:12:11,919 --> 00:12:12,879
will be Company Commander.

245
00:12:14,679 --> 00:12:15,399
Thank you, Brigade Commander.

246
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:17,240
Dongsheng,

247
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:19,679
I'll

248
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:20,879
reward you fifty silver dollars.

249
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:21,879
Take a month off.

250
00:12:22,039 --> 00:12:22,679
Recover from your injuries.

251
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:23,559
When you come back,

252
00:12:24,159 --> 00:12:24,919
you'll be a Platoon Leader.

253
00:12:25,559 --> 00:12:26,200
Thank you, Brigade Commander.

254
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,639
Sit down, sit down.

255
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,080
Eat.

256
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,559
Company Commander Shui.

257
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,600
Why are you here?

258
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,960
Don't we have servants for that?

259
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:53,799
Servants can't serve the Brigade Commander.

260
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:55,679
Right, right, right.

261
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:56,720
Brother-in-law.

262
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,039
Look at our Qiuying.

263
00:12:58,039 --> 00:12:59,200
Hasn't she grown up nicely?

264
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:00,480
Mature.

265
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:01,120
Yes, very mature.

266
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,960
And who is this young lady?

267
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,399
Reporting, Brigade Commander.

268
00:13:05,759 --> 00:13:06,399
This is

269
00:13:06,639 --> 00:13:07,960
my brother-in-law's daughter.

270
00:13:08,639 --> 00:13:09,440
Her name is Qiuying.

271
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,200
Greetings, Brigade Commander.

272
00:13:14,159 --> 00:13:15,159
You're a Company Commander now.

273
00:13:15,399 --> 00:13:16,159
A perfect match in status.

274
00:13:16,399 --> 00:13:17,399
Hurry up and propose.

275
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,200
That's not appropriate, is it?

276
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,159
Why not?

277
00:13:22,159 --> 00:13:23,159
The Brigade Commander is happy right now.

278
00:13:23,279 --> 00:13:24,200
He can make it happen for you.

279
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:24,799
Hurry.

280
00:13:25,559 --> 00:13:27,159
How could the County Magistrate refuse him?

281
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:31,840
Take a sip.

282
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:33,399
Brigade Commander.

283
00:13:33,519 --> 00:13:34,120
A perfect match.
